
dGPU crashing - MES FW version must be larger than 0x63 to support limit single process feature
https://gitlab.freedesktop.org/drm/amd/-/issues/4083


Subject: [PATCH] drm/amdgpu/mes11: optimize MES pipe FW version fetching

Don't fetch it again if we already have it.  It seems the
don't reliably have the proper value at resume in some
cases.

Closes: https://gitlab.freedesktop.org/drm/amd/-/issues/4083
Signed-off-by: Alex Deucher <alexander.deucher@xxxxxxxxxx>
---
 drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/mes_v11_0.c | 4 ++++
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/mes_v11_0.c b/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/mes_v11_0.c
index 16f8bc36afa07..06b51867c9aac 100644
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/mes_v11_0.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/mes_v11_0.c
@@ -859,6 +859,10 @@ static void mes_v11_0_get_fw_version(struct amdgpu_device *adev)
 {
 	int pipe;
 
+	/* return early if we have already fetched these */
+	if (adev->mes.sched_version && adev->mes.kiq_version)
+		return;
+
 	/* get MES scheduler/KIQ versions */
 	mutex_lock(&adev->srbm_mutex);
 
-- 
